“Basically, a healthy skin is like cling film. If you put a drop of water on it, the water drop will roll down
the film. Atopic dermatitis skin is like blotting paper. When you put a drop of water, it is absorbed. The only existing
treatment to restore the skin barrier is to apply everyday on the skin, an emollient that will fill all the little holes
contained in the blotting paper.”

On the occasion of World Atopic Eczema Day, we met with Professor Jean-François Nicolas, Dermatologist and
Professor of Immunology in Lyon, France.

on how to live normally with this disease.

UVA rays cause immediate pigmentation, darkening your skin within minutes and accelerating collagen alteration & premature aging. UVB rays trigger delayed pigmentation, leading to uneven skin and long-term hyperpigmentation. Both types of pigmentation indicate signs of UV penetration—not a “healthy glow.” That’s why daily SPF is non-negotiable. Photoderm Crème SPF 50+ provides reinforced UVA & UVB protection, shielding your skin from immediate & long-term damage while keeping your complexion even and radiant.

Did you know that NAOS is a committed brand? For NAOS, the impact of our sun protection products on the health of all ecosystems is a priority. Water is a fundamental resource for living beings, and because it is at the heart of all our products, we pay particular attention to aquatic ecosystems. This is directly illustrated in our formulation charter, through the selection of our ingredients and the stringent ecotoxicity tests we carry out.

At NAOS, 100% of our sun care products are tested through continuous environmental impact analyses, using three different and complementary methods.A method based on the viability of corals allowing to observe the retraction of polyps and the bleaching of cuttings. In this case, the toxicity of the molecules is measured both for the microalgae that live in symbiosis with the corals and for the corals that also represent the upstream animals of the marine food chains.

Bioderma is a NAOS brand
